  - S043 Long-Baseline Auditor (Claude subagent, Explore tool) quantified "post-engine-v4 Path-A concentration at 47% (S024–S042) vs 0% (S001–S023)" — epoch-specific pattern.
  - This is suggestive-not-conclusive evidence of operator's observation: the post-v5 cadence is dominated by short-cycle watch/housekeeping work, with substantive content events spaced more irregularly. Whether the 6-session retention-window is causally linked to this pattern vs. merely coincident with engine-maturation is the empirical question.

**Consequence for S045**: scope B is substantive — it proposes revising `read-contract.md` §2c values (retention-window count). Revision would be a substantive spec amendment (engine-v7 → engine-v8 bump candidate). Choice space: (i) activate §5.9 10-session (literal preserved direction); (ii) revise to a larger value than 10 (operator's "long-term view" framing may warrant more); (iii) introduce a tiered-retention mechanism (e.g., last-6 full + older-closes read-as-headers); (iv) defer revision pending empirical test of alternative (a one-session experiment with manually-expanded window); (v) preserve at 6 with a new diagnostic (operator observation recorded as forward observation, no revision). Multi-perspective deliberation warranted given substantive nature.

