prompts/development.md:19:Begin by reading the workspace's default-read surface completely: the workspace-identity marker `MODE.md` (per `specifications/read-contract.md` v4 §1 item 0), the active specifications (per `specifications/engine-manifest.md` §3), the current `SESSION-LOG.md` index, the current `open-issues/index.md`, each close within the §2c 6-session retention window, and — when the file exists — `engine-feedback/INDEX.md` for operator-mediated engine-feedback inbox (per `read-contract.md` v4 §1 item 9). Then enumerate the archive-surface records relevant to this session's subject matter; for each, either read it in full via its archive manifest + chunk references, or declare in the session's honest-limits section why it was not read and what gap that leaves. The default-read and archive surface enumerations are specified canonically in `specifications/read-contract.md`. Build a full picture of what exists before changing anything.
prompts/development.md:27:Before doing any substantive work, consult the workspace's record of prior decisions: `SESSION-LOG.md` entries, `open-issues/` status files, and — for any decision load-bearing to this session's work — the relevant `02-decisions.md` and any archive-surface records it references (via the `[archive: path]` convention per `read-contract.md` §6). If an idea was considered and rejected earlier, do not silently re-propose it. If you believe a rejected idea deserves reconsideration, cite the prior rejection and explain what has changed. Continuity of reasoning is the whole point of preserving provenance.
prompts/development.md:35:**File-edit claim discipline (added engine-v7 per WX-35-1 forward convention).** At session close, for every file named in the close narrative §1e "development-provenance files amended" (or equivalent), the Case Steward verifies via `git log --oneline <path>` (or equivalent) that the claimed edit was actually committed during the session. If the edit is verified, the claim stands. If the edit was not committed (for whatever reason — omission, revert, out-of-scope), the close narrative must explicitly state "claim retracted; file not edited this session". This convention prevents propagation of claimed-but-unexecuted edits across session boundaries (the Session 035 WX-35-1 pattern: 13 sessions of SESSION-LOG rows claiming OI-004.md edits that were never committed).
prompts/application.md:3:Selvedge is the methodology (abstract approach). The Selvedge engine is its current loadable implementation. This application is one specific run of that engine; it has its own inputs, its own artefacts, its own validation pathway, and its own provenance. The engine's development-provenance (the `SESSION-LOG.md`, `open-issues.md`, and `provenance/` of the source workspace where the engine was developed) is NOT part of this application's context unless explicitly imported by a decision in this workspace.
prompts/application.md:43:- **Workspace reading** — the default-read surface of this application's workspace (this workspace, not the engine's source workspace). This is the set enumerated in `read-contract.md` §1, scoped to this application: active-status specifications, the `SESSION-LOG.md` index, `open-issues/index.md`, every prior session's `03-close.md`, the currently-active session's provenance directory, PROMPT.md / `prompts/development.md` / `prompts/application.md`, and `applications/`. The archive surface (raw perspective records from closed sessions, superseded specification versions, over-budget annotations preserved as archive-packs) is read by explicit reference — `[archive: path]` citations — as the session's work requires.
prompts/application.md:67:Provenance accumulates in `provenance/NNN-<slug>/` as in the self-development application. `SESSION-LOG.md` is a thin one-line-per-session index per `workspace-structure.md` v4 §SESSION-LOG.md. `open-issues/` is a directory with per-OI files (`OI-NNN.md`) plus `index.md` per `workspace-structure.md` v4 §open-issues. At session close, the orchestrator verifies the default-read budget (`read-contract.md` §8); any current-session raw exceeding the per-file ceiling is archive-packed per `read-contract.md` §9.
