./provenance/022-workspace-scaling-trajectory/archive/pre-R8a-SESSION-LOG/00-source.md:20:| 016 | 2026-04-22 | Operator Reframing Input — OI-017 Opened; D-072 Preserved | Ran `tools/validate.sh` at start (363 pass, 0 fail — seventh consecutive clean session-opener run). Session 016 received a session-open operator input (preserved verbatim at `provenance/016-operator-reframing-assessment/00-operator-input.md`) proposing a **structural reframing**: the workspace may be better understood as an **engine** (defined inputs, procedures, outputs) rather than as a methodology in the abstract. Two structural consequences offered as input rather than direction: (1) distinguishability of the engine's executable definition from development provenance; (2) distinct execution prompts for different applications of the engine. Operator explicitly stated resolution is not required this session; any file including PROMPT.md may be modified; tools may be installed via `uv tool`; agenda to be determined accordingly. Audit of Session 015 synthesis fidelity: clean on both auditable dimensions (four cited raw-output line references in `015-session-assessment/00-assessment.md` §2 all verified against Session 014 files; D-072 `[none]` triggers declaration consistent with decision's content per Q7). **Single-perspective session** (no deliberation; scope-appropriate per Session 015 D-072 precedent — this is a surveying + hypothesising response to operator input, not an originated design output). Per PROMPT.md anti-silent-import rule and OI-015 laundering-enforcement requirement, operator input surfaced through explicit §3 surveying step (six related framings across traditions — closest fit: interpreter-vs-interpreted-program) and §4 hypothesising step (three competing hypotheses H1 no reframing / H2 full reframing / H3 partial reframing, each with gains, losses, strongest-advocate-position-hypothesised). Surveying identified the word "methodology" is used in two distinct senses across the active specifications (abstract-approach vs. concrete-implementation) — a latent ambiguity now surfaced for deliberation. **One decision (D-073)** declaring `**Triggers met:** [none]` with triggers rationale: ratifies Option α (assessment-only; defer Cell 1; open OI-017); preserves D-072 precommitment with re-disposition (Session 017 default is Cell 1 per D-072 unless user elects OI-017 deliberation first). **OI-017 opened** (engine-vs-methodology reframing): activation trigger "first session electing to deliberate"; preferred starting point H1/H2/H3 frame with explicit permission for additional hypotheses; D-023-triggering deliberation requires non-Claude participation (kernel revision is possible under H2/H3; PROMPT.md revision is significant-event per workspace-structure.md). **OI-017 is the first open issue surfaced from external operator input rather than from the methodology's own self-deliberation** — a novel origin kind recorded in OI-007 annotation. OI-007 count 12 → 13. **No spec changes; no external artefact; no OI state changes beyond OI-017 opening** (OI-016 remains Resolved-provisional; OI-004 tally 5-of-3 unchanged; criterion-3 cumulative 40; voluntary:required ratio 5:5 unchanged). No new watchpoints opened (OI-007 scaling pressure argues against redundant WX-16-\*; audit findings tracked within OI-017 or §2). No tool installation exercised (operator `uv tool` authorisation recorded but not needed this session); no PROMPT.md revision exercised (operator revision-authorisation recorded but single-perspective revision would be specification violation per workspace-structure.md significant-event rule; deferred to OI-017 deliberation). OI-009 G/O/K/S evaluation passes all four criteria (external-frame translation + external-action-decision-space narrowing + external-reader visibility + specific-obstacle resolution). Session 016 work-shape extends Session 007 (external-application preparation) and Session 015 (reference-validation agenda ratification) precedents for legitimate planning-only session-shape responding to external input. Session 017 should: run `tools/validate.sh` at start; audit Session 016 synthesis fidelity (narrower surface — verify §2 Session-015 audit consistency; verify §3 word-usage survey accurate across specifications; verify D-073 `[none]` declaration consistency; verify OI-017 activation trigger and preferred starting point operationally meaningful); execute Option A Cell 1 per D-072 default unless user steers to OI-017 deliberation first. OI-017 deliberation path (if ratified): convene 3–4 perspectives with at least one adversarial Skeptic (inheriting Session 012 refuse-to-name minority is natural) plus one non-Claude Outsider per D-023_1; deliberate H1/H2/H3 with permission for additional hypotheses; decision venue for any PROMPT.md revision, kernel revision, or new `engine-manifest.md` specification creation. |
